16/06/2004
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- Council of Europe Secretary General Walter Schwimmer urged the Organisation of the Islamic Conference (OIC) on Tuesday (15 June) to end the isolation imposed on the Turkish Cypriot community. 
Schwimmer was delivering a speech at the OIC ministerial meeting in Istanbul. 
Turkish Cypriot Foreign Minister Serdar Denktash later called on participants to accept the "Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus" (TRNC) as a full member of the organisation and to help lift embargoes imposed on the TRNC. 
(Anadolu Agency, Turkish Daily News, TRT 2 - 15/06/04)
